In article <1pq0re$gc2@network.ucsd.edu>, loki@sdphu3.ucsd.edu (Lance M Cottrell) writes:
|> Norton Utilities for the Mac has a disk wipe program which
|> claims to do just that.  It wipes all free space including
|> empty space at the end of partialy filled blocks.  It also
|> has a three pass "government" mode.

And, of course, so does Norton Utilities for the PC. It refers to the
ends of partially used blocks as "slack space". You can clear them
with the "wipeinfo" command; just be certain you request that only the
slack space be wiped, not entire files...

